parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: Probably a fuller form of rheo; an alternate for epo in certain tenses; to utter, i.e. Speak or say.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Dative 1st Person Singular
str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.
Therefore, then. Apparently a primary word; certainly, or accordingly.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Accusative Neuter Singular
str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Middle or Passive - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To blame, censure, find fault. Middle voice of an apparently primary verb; to blame.
For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.

parse: Verb - Perfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To set against; I withstand, resist, oppose. From anti and histemi; to stand against, i.e. Oppose.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
Will, counsel, purpose. From boulomai; a resolve.
